<task id="028" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>Phase A Integration Test — Vertical-Slice of All 4 Pillars</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>005, 013, 023, 025</dependencies>
    <blocks>029</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, integration-test, ai, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Integration test only; new test files; tags include `integration-test`; per CLAUDE.md §8 STANDARD rigor for testing tasks.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Gate task; runs after all Phase A pillars complete; sequential before exit gate (029).</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build a vertical-slice integration test exercising all 4 Phase A pillars end-to-end:
    persona scope resolution (Pillar 1), data-driven tools (Pillar 2), generic
    `invoke_playbook` (Pillar 3), and chat /summarize routing through
    `PlaybookExecutionEngine` (Pillar 4).

    Critical-path context: this test is the integration gate before Phase A exit (task 029).
    It validates that all 4 pillars compose correctly — not just individually, but
    together in a realistic chat session. Per spec §6 Vertical-Slice Validation Target,
    Phase D's full vertical-slice ALSO exercises every Phase A pillar; this Phase A test
    is the early canary.

    Test scenario: in a single chat session, (a) tenant CUST- persona resolves correctly
    via `IScopeResolverService` (Pillar 1); (b) chat-agent tool list includes the data-driven
    rows (Pillar 2 incl. 10 migrated tools); (c) `/summarize` user input invokes the
    generic `invoke_playbook` tool (Pillar 3); (d) the invocation routes through
    `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync("summarize-document-for-chat@v1", ...)` (Pillar 4);
    (e) the FK chain `playbook → node → action` traverses cleanly; (f) safety pipeline
    middleware applied; (g) conversational primacy preserved.

    No new code beyond tests. No new ADRs. No deployment changes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF QA engineer experienced with vertical-slice integration tests + the Spaarke
    chat-agent pipeline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Vertical-slice integration test exercises all 4 Phase A pillars in a single chat
    session. Test passes; evidence recorded; Phase A exit gate unblocked.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="chat-architecture">docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="playbook-architecture">docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Test verifies telemetry payloads contain only tool/playbook/node IDs + decisions + timestamps; no user message content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (tests only).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-01">Conversational primacy preserved through Phase A vertical slice.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">Safety pipeline middleware chain applied at every step.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-08">11 production node executors unchanged.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff-api/integration-test</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD — vertical-slice integration test; tests-only addition".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 005 ✅ + 013 ✅ + 023 ✅ + 025 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Author Integration Test">
      In `tests/integration/`, add `PhaseAVerticalSliceTests.cs`. Test scenario covers all 4 pillars in sequence (per &lt;prompt&gt; scenario). Use real DI graph + staged Dataverse rows.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Verify Each Pillar Step">
      The test asserts at each step: (Pillar 1) persona resolved from `sprk_aipersona` row; (Pillar 2) tool list includes data-driven rows; (Pillar 3) `/summarize` triggers `invoke_playbook`; (Pillar 4) routes through engine (no alternate-key lookup).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify Cross-Cutting Concerns">
      Assert: safety pipeline middleware applied at every step (NFR-13); conversational primacy retained (NFR-01); 11 node executors unchanged (NFR-08); telemetry ADR-015-compliant.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Run Test">
      Execute test in CI environment. MUST pass. If fails: report which pillar's step broke; do NOT continue to 029 until fixed.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk each criterion; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 028 ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to 029. Report Phase A vertical-slice readiness.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (integration)</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit test additions</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/PhaseAVerticalSliceTests.cs (NEW)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (028 🔲 → ✅)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/current-task.md (reset to 029)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-028-vertical-slice-evidence.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Integration test exercises all 4 Phase A pillars in a single chat session.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pillar 1: persona resolved from `sprk_aipersona` (with appropriate scope hierarchy).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pillar 2: chat-agent tool list comes from `sprk_analysistool` rows (data-driven).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pillar 3: `/summarize` invokes generic `invoke_playbook` tool.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pillar 4: invocation routes through `PlaybookExecutionEngine` (no alternate-key lookup).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Safety pipeline middleware chain applied (NFR-13).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Conversational primacy preserved (NFR-01).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">11 production node executors unchanged (NFR-08).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Telemetry payloads ADR-015-compliant (no user content).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Test passes in CI; evidence captured.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
